title: New rocket motor for U.S. Air Force ICBM completes ground test
summary: Northrop Grumman announced Jan. 16 it conducted a successful static fire test of the second-stage solid rocket motor for a new intercontinental ballistic missile the company is developing for the U.S. Air Force.

title: Space investment rebounded in 2023 with heavy sector M&A, report says
summary: Investment in the space sector bounced back last year, rebounding closer to the record high of 2021, according to a report Tuesday by New York-based Space Capital.

title: Vulcan launch demonstrates new solid rocket boosters
summary: The first launch of United Launch Alliance’s Vulcan Centaur was also a successful demonstration of new solid rocket boosters developed by Northrop Grumman for the vehicle.
